column2: Over 5" rain last week- sunny- brown water entering via small creek- ripple
Overcast- moderate waves- no bloom- level dropped 6" since 5/9- surface temp 67 F
About .5" rain in last 10 days- has been clear- water more brown than usual
Partly cloudy- hot- humid- light E wind- algae bloom.  Water level: up 2"
Overcast- light drizzle- calm- algae bloom on S end- but not at testing site
Partly cloudy- over 3" of rain the previous week- moderate wave action- algae bloom on calm days- heavy weed growth
Clear- moderate wave action- surface temp: 71 F- algae blooms on calm days
Cloudy- moderate waves- algae mixed w/a brownish color
Partly cloudy- light breeze- about 5" rain in past week- algae bloom in upper part of lake.  Water level: Up 3.5"
Bright- slight breeze- surface temp: 58 F- lake normally down 6-8" every fall
Recent rains + wind have stirred the lake. overcast with slight wave action.
Warm- dry spell over the last two weeks have cleared lake- quite a bit of pollen near shores.
Weather warming after a spell of very cool weather for June.  Little if any algal blooms.
Very minor levels of algal- weather has been cool and wet.
Some algae build up in the last 6 days- weather is clear- strong south winds.  Temp is in the high 80's- water temp is 74 @ surface.
Draw down due to dam repair.  Algae levels up some since last sample- rainfall at upper end of lake has to be sparse.
Highest algae level this season.  Heavy rain and violent storm might account for poor clarity reading- surface temp is 65- slightly overcast slight wind.
Weather is overcast- slight breeze- on and off showers- for past week and up to 1.5" of rainfall.  Some algae blooms- surface temp is 62 degrees.
Clear sky- no wind- surface temp is 58 degrees- good weather the last 5 days- water is the clearest its been all year.
Wide swings in temperature seem to turn lake over a couple of times.  Unusual for water to be brown color.
Some algal blooms- surface water temp 56- approximately 2in. of rain last few days
Algal bloom blown into shoreline- weed growth 2-3 weeks behind normal- little sunshine past 10 days- 3-4" rain past 10 days
2.5" rain past week- water surface temp 70- weed growth approximately 2-3 weeks behind normal year- Bluegills spawning.
Cloudy cool weather has dropped water surface temps back to 70- weed beds in deeper water (10-12') have not developed
Steady warm weather with little rain last couple of weeks- water is clearing.
Cool weather- has dropped surface temperature to 62 degrees- strong winds last week tore many weeds loose- now floating near the shore.
Ice out April 17- water cloudy since then- snow last week.
Very little rain during the past two weeks.  Seems to have cleared lake water.  Weed growth just starting.
Dry warm weather continues to keep water clear-weed growth in shallow (8' or less) is rapid.  Deeper (10'+) still slow.
Storms yesterday + early this a.m. might have clouded water a bit- lake level up about 2.5 - 3" in the last  two days- weather overcast- wind about 10 mph
Weather has been very good-past 10 days-very little rain-decrease in clarity since last sample.
Heavy overcast- light mist- 3.25" of rain in the past 7 days.  Secchi depth less than last time
Some algal blooms- past okay- weather is warm and dry.
Some algal blooms near the shore- weather is warm- rainfall is normal- surface water is starting to cool.
This section of the lake has not turned over- Thermocline at approx. 26'- good oxygen above this level- great deal of rain lately- max. depth this part of lake since '68.
Lake normally draw down 4" tab- in fall- weather is overcast- on-off drizzle typical last few days.
Sampling done two days after 1"+ rainfall-rather cool + dry.  Spring-ice went out April 23.
Hot + dry weather for 7 days.  Some algae in shallow bays.  Poor oxygen in water 2' or less.
Heavy overcast today.  Surface temp. 69 degrees F.  Down 12 degrees F from a few weeks ago-rain 1" and cool weather past week.
1.5" rain past week May have clouded water slightly-weed growth heavier than last year.
Highest algae level since 1988-6.5" rain past 8 days + hot + humid weather past month.
Algae starting to diminish-cool day.  Weather seems to help-surface temp. 68 degrees F.
Ice off May 1.  Brownish tint- normal this time of year.
Surface temp. 74 degrees. rain brought junk in from mud lake into site e.
1.4" rain 10 hours prior cloudy slight breeze.
Sunny- breezy- N wind- 40 degrees F.
Sunny- slight breeze- SW wind- 62 degrees.
Sunny- some clouds- S wind- 70 degrees.  Breezy.
Overcast- damp- some fog- and the air temperature is 60 degrees.
Some sun- cloudy- cool- and moderate wind.
Some clouds- southwest breeze- warm- and sunny.
Clear- warm- some clouds- and slight breeze.
Cloudy- very hazy- very warm and humid- and very still.
Cloudy- some sun- very cool- and calm.
Cloudy- some sun- breezy- and the temperature is 43 degrees.
Cloudy- 78 degrees F- and very breezy.
Some clouds- sunny- temperature is 75 degrees- slight breeze- 3.5" of rain the previous day.
2" of rain on 8/3- partly cloudy- some breeze- and the temperature is 68 degrees.
Very cloudy- breezy- snow on ground- temperature is 0 degrees C - 32 degrees F.
Sunny- partly cloudy- upper 50s temperature. Calm- white clouds.
Cloudy- some sun- slight rain early AM- cool- slight breeze- 68 F.
Clear- partly white cloudy.  Sunny- low 40s. Breezy- cool.
Warm- windy.  Very windy.  Could not hold boat in position for balance of tests.
D.O. readings not available - was testing new Hach Quanta meter -but wasn't calibrated right.

cloudy- breezy. Rained 3/4 in. last night
sunning- light breeze Nice day light breeze Nice day- light breeze
